&= \pm \tfrac{3x - 6y + 2z + 5 + 4x - 12y + 3z - 3}{\sqrt{49}\sqrt{181}}\\
&= \pm \tfrac{7x - 18y + 5z + 2}{7\sqrt{181}} \\
&= x - \tfrac{18}{7}y + \tfrac{5}{7}z + \tfrac{2}{7\sqrt{181}}
\end{align*}
<answer>So, the equation of the bisecting plane is $x - \tfrac{18}{7}y + \tfrac{5}{7}z + \tfrac{2}{7\sqrt{181}} = 0.$</answer>

